1
00:00:01,564 --> 00:00:04,397
(Multicom Jingle)

2
00:00:13,266 --> 00:00:18,266
(dramatic orchestral music)
(strong wind blows)

3
00:00:32,465 --> 00:00:34,011
- Papa.

4
00:00:34,011 --> 00:00:37,928
(melancholic orchestral music)

5
00:01:28,539 --> 00:01:33,539
♪ Someone's falling asleep tonight ♪

6
00:01:34,175 --> 00:01:39,175
♪ Sandman, I'm talking to you ♪

7
00:01:40,158 --> 00:01:45,158
♪ This little girl has
just turned off her light ♪

8
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:50,433
♪ Make sure her dreams
are a colorful sight ♪

9
00:01:50,632 --> 00:01:55,632
♪ Chase all the fear from
her bedside tonight ♪

10
00:01:58,139 --> 00:02:01,722
♪ Tomorrow is not far away ♪

11
00:02:04,284 --> 00:02:05,117
- Cut!

12
00:02:05,117 --> 00:02:06,920
Cut, playback.
(bell rings)

13
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:08,970
Hello, Mr. Snow Man?

14
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:10,000
I have a blizzard going here.

15
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,700
Mr. Snow Man, I have
a blizzard going here.

16
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:15,560
I need a lot more snow, say
50% more snow, you got that?

17
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,393
- Jane!

18
00:02:20,378 --> 00:02:21,961
- [Jane] Your turn.

19
00:02:23,422 --> 00:02:26,180
- When do I get to play a
real part instead of just

20
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:29,680
being your stand-in or hangin'
around in the background?

21
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,850
- Maybe when I think you're ready.

22
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:33,123
- [Director] Come on, Blanche.

23
00:02:34,420 --> 00:02:36,070
- Maybe you'd better go with her.

24
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:41,790
- [Director] Alright, going one more time.

25
00:02:41,790 --> 00:02:43,576
I need some help, people,
we gotta make this thing.

26
00:02:43,576 --> 00:02:45,150
Let's go, let's go!

27
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:47,263
- Honey, the parts will get bigger.

28
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:50,140
- Not in her pictures.

29
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:53,030
I really, really don't understand her.

30
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:55,580
Sometimes she's nice and
then she gets really mean.

31
00:02:56,559 --> 00:02:57,663
I think she's crazy.

32
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:01,822
The way she treats everybody,
even you and Daddy.

33
00:03:01,822 --> 00:03:05,077
- Please, we need you on your
sister's marks, thank you.

34
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,730
- We promised your
sister a real part, Jane.

35
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:19,219
- We did, Jane.

36
00:03:19,219 --> 00:03:21,390
- Blanche is clumsy.

37
00:03:21,390 --> 00:03:22,223
- [Director] Okay, Blanche.

38
00:03:22,223 --> 00:03:24,560
Take your sister's position
on the bed, please.

39
00:03:47,616 --> 00:03:50,866
- Whoa, whoa, sky bombers, sky bombers!

40
00:03:55,654 --> 00:03:57,941
- I'd like to live at the beach always.

41
00:03:57,941 --> 00:03:59,444
- Maybe we could!

42
00:03:59,444 --> 00:04:00,667
- Daddy?

43
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:03,030
- No, Blanche, it's just
too far from the studios.

44
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:05,222
- It might be nice for the girls.

45
00:04:05,222 --> 00:04:08,600
- Yeah, but when Blanche
begins her acting lessons,

46
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:10,500
it'll be just too inconvenient.

47
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:14,737
- Now me, and let's do it like Betty Boop.

48
00:04:14,737 --> 00:04:15,570
- Okay.

49
00:04:17,312 --> 00:04:18,985
Get your nose.

50
00:04:18,985 --> 00:04:21,722
(girls giggle)

51
00:04:21,722 --> 00:04:23,113
Okay.

52
00:04:23,113 --> 00:04:25,635
Put your lips together.

53
00:04:25,635 --> 00:04:27,718
(laughs)

54
00:04:30,709 --> 00:04:32,455
(father laughs)

55
00:04:32,455 --> 00:04:35,001
- Good job, Blanche, good job!
(Blanche yelps and giggles)

56
00:04:35,001 --> 00:04:40,001
Good job. (laughs)
(bell rings)

57
00:04:41,891 --> 00:04:43,133
- Ice cream!
- Ice cream?

58
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:45,159
Oh, oh, oh, ice cream, ice cream.

59
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:50,159
We scream, we all scream, oh!
(somber orchestral music)

60
00:05:31,661 --> 00:05:34,244
- I know, but I didn't know what to do.

61
00:05:34,244 --> 00:05:38,911
You'd gone and I didn't think
you were ever coming back.

62
00:05:55,794 --> 00:05:59,723
You won't leave, now that you're here?

63
00:05:59,723 --> 00:06:02,433
- No.
- You promise you'll stay?

64
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:03,266
- Always.

65
00:06:05,671 --> 00:06:06,588
- Oh, Bill.

66
00:06:08,883 --> 00:06:09,716
Bill.

67
00:06:14,797 --> 00:06:16,730
Ah, I didn't hear you come in.

68
00:06:16,730 --> 00:06:20,259
- How could you, with
that damn thing blaring?

69
00:06:20,259 --> 00:06:21,092
- Bill.

70
00:06:23,212 --> 00:06:24,045
Bill.

71
00:06:26,238 --> 00:06:27,660
- That one of your turkeys?

72
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:32,367
- I can see so many things
Tony could've improved upon,

73
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:34,703
that would've, might've helped the movie.

74
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:37,310
- Like not releasing it, you mean.

75
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:38,573
- Oh, it wasn't that bad.

76
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:43,400
Host of the series says
they're making some videos

77
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,260
out of my movies.
- Really?

78
00:06:46,910 --> 00:06:49,610
- Jane, Jane, would you
please get a video recorder?

79
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:51,923
I've asked you so many
times, it would be fun.

80
00:06:53,373 --> 00:06:55,290
I wanna see some old movies.
- Oh, great.

81
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:57,810
We could have a film festival
of your films, Blanche.

82
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:59,153
- No need to be sarcastic.

83
00:07:00,260 --> 00:07:03,220
Anyway, you seem to have
forgotten that you had parts

84
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:04,547
in most of my movies.

85
00:07:05,910 --> 00:07:10,190
- They weren't parts, Blanche,
they were scraps, leftovers.

86
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:12,210
- Some of them were big.

87
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:15,040
- And then cut to nothing,
you took care of that.

88
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,270
You, the editor, the director,
you were in it together.

89
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:20,170
- That's not true.
- Yeah, that is true, Blanche.

90
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,400
Yeah, you shot my scenes,

91
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,210
so I could be cut out of the film later.

92
00:07:23,210 --> 00:07:24,080
Yeah, I know that trick.

93
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:26,487
You seem to forget I was a star
when your billing was still

94
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:28,567
"pioneer child killed by stampede."

95
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,040
Just really glad that Daddy never lived

96
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,847
to see what you did to my career.

97
00:07:36,045 --> 00:07:39,378
(man whistles jauntily)

98
00:07:43,784 --> 00:07:48,784
(collar rattles)
(dog barks)

99
00:07:48,855 --> 00:07:50,123
(dog barks)
- Tweak!

100
00:07:51,130 --> 00:07:52,780
Come here, boy, come here, come on.

101
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:56,550
That's my baby boy.
- Frank, Frank.

102
00:07:56,550 --> 00:07:58,350
Come over here, quick, quick, quick!

103
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:01,490
Do you know who that is?

104
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,973
- I wanted to die, I
couldn't face it alone.

105
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,235
- No.

106
00:08:10,235 --> 00:08:11,435
- That's Blanche Hudson.

107
00:08:13,697 --> 00:08:14,530
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

108
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:19,510
Don't be so smug, you love
living nextdoor to a movie star.

109
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:21,760
- Sweetheart, I wouldn't
know her if I fell over her.

110
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,363
I've hardly ever seen her.

111
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,257
- I saw her, I did, I saw her once.

112
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:29,740
Frank, Frank, I'm watchin' the TV.

113
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:31,570
- You know, the only one
I've ever seen is that sister

114
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:33,880
draggin' herself around like
a ratty old flower child.

115
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,713
- Now, be nice.

116
00:08:34,713 --> 00:08:36,290
- She looks like she got
trampled at Woodstock.

117
00:08:36,290 --> 00:08:39,230
- Shh!
(Frank laughs)

118
00:08:39,230 --> 00:08:41,520
- [Frank] I heard she was a lush.

119
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,480
- Do you know that I got one
of those trashy newspapers

120
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,440
from the supermarket.

121
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:47,080
They did a whole week
on Where Are They Now?

122
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:50,460
It said that Jane Hudson
deliberately tried to kill

123
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:53,520
her sister Blanche in
that so-called accident

124
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,813
and only succeeded in paralyzing her.

125
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:58,923
- Now, please!

126
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,503
Oh, please, can I have the TV?

127
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,593
- Nope.

128
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,073
Watch upstairs, I got work to do.

129
00:09:14,335 --> 00:09:17,002
(Blanche moans)

130
00:09:39,290 --> 00:09:40,123
- Bye bye.

131
00:09:53,490 --> 00:09:55,710
Jane, did you take your pills?

132
00:09:55,710 --> 00:09:57,160
- You'll miss your big scene.

133
00:10:10,489 --> 00:10:13,572
(moody string music)

134
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,232
Ow.

135
00:11:23,258 --> 00:11:24,091
Ow.

136
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:51,573
- Miss Hudson, I'm Connie
Trotter from right next door.

137
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:56,040
I don't mean to bother you,
but I was just making some

138
00:11:56,040 --> 00:12:00,220
cookies and after seeing
your sister's film on TV,

139
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:02,520
I couldn't resist sharing
what I do real well

140
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,970
to thank your sister for
what she does real well.

141
00:12:08,408 --> 00:12:10,108
(chuckles) I kinda rehearsed that.

142
00:12:14,050 --> 00:12:15,560
Did you know that there's a retrospective

143
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:18,196
of your sister's films on?
- Yeah, I know.

144
00:12:18,196 --> 00:12:23,196
- Um, you know, I have a video
cassette of Dark Sunrise,

145
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:26,710
the movie that your sister
did with William Carol.

146
00:12:26,710 --> 00:12:29,480
I was pretty young when all
your sister's films came out,

147
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:33,920
but I have become a real fan
through TV and I was wondering

148
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,900
if maybe she was--
- She doesn't give autographs.

149
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:37,420
If that's what you're after.

150
00:12:37,420 --> 00:12:40,660
- Oh, would you and your
sister like to come over

151
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:41,720
to our house for dinner some night?

152
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:44,160
My husband and I would really like that.

153
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:47,233
- I don't go out much and she
doesn't go out at all anymore.

154
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:50,060
Thanks for the cookies.

155
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:52,780
- You have to hold the
bottom of the bag, because,

156
00:12:52,780 --> 00:12:53,903
because it's greasy.

157
00:12:57,247 --> 00:12:59,333
- "Dear Miss Blanche Hudson.

158
00:13:00,457 --> 00:13:03,607
"My mother told me to
watch your old films.

159
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:05,887
"And I did.

160
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:09,118
"And I was..."

161
00:13:09,118 --> 00:13:11,201
(laughs)

162
00:13:14,861 --> 00:13:16,677
(dog whines)

163
00:13:16,677 --> 00:13:17,753
- Frank, Frank.

164
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:21,663
I just went over there,
right, and I brought her...

165
00:13:26,056 --> 00:13:26,889
- Jane!

166
00:13:32,499 --> 00:13:33,990
(phone rings)
Jane?

167
00:13:33,990 --> 00:13:36,137
Jane, would you come up here, please?

168
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:49,873
- What is it now?

169
00:13:49,873 --> 00:13:50,733
- Come here.

170
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:04,677
Jane, was that our
nextdoor neighbor I heard?

171
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:07,233
- [Jane] You didn't
wanna see her, did you?

172
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:08,440
- I could've said hello.

173
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:10,120
- When they moved in, you
said they were gawking at you

174
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,980
in the backyard, you
didn't wanna see anybody.

175
00:14:11,980 --> 00:14:14,090
- That was six months ago, I looked awful.

176
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:17,143
- You don't look any better now. (laughs)

177
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,713
- Could you wash my hair?

178
00:14:25,649 --> 00:14:27,193
Oh, do something different.

179
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:32,070
Do you remember when we were
kids we used to go to the ocean

180
00:14:32,070 --> 00:14:35,480
we'd get sandy and we'd come
back and we'd get showered

181
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:39,763
and I'd do your hair
and then you'd do mine.

182
00:14:42,432 --> 00:14:43,265
- Yes.

183
00:14:48,026 --> 00:14:49,510
- Why do you always try to hurt me?

184
00:14:49,510 --> 00:14:50,713
- I didn't say anything.

185
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:54,933
- It's unfair.

186
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,862
It was just an accident,
I've never blamed you.

187
00:14:58,862 --> 00:15:00,302
- I don't wanna talk about the accident.

188
00:15:00,302 --> 00:15:03,385
- I've never blamed you for anything.

189
00:15:05,755 --> 00:15:07,483
(hairdryer blows)

190
00:15:07,483 --> 00:15:09,900
(both laugh)

191
00:15:15,967 --> 00:15:20,130
- [Jane] Do you remember,
at the beach, we would get

192
00:15:20,130 --> 00:15:23,403
on Daddy's shoulders and
one of us on one shoulder--

193
00:15:23,403 --> 00:15:27,273
- And he would walk out into
the water as far as he could,

194
00:15:27,273 --> 00:15:29,632
and the waves would hit us!

195
00:15:29,632 --> 00:15:32,049
(both laugh)

196
00:15:33,977 --> 00:15:37,260
- And then he'd fall and we'd laugh!

197
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:39,063
Oh, god, how we laughed.

198
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:48,877
- Can I look?

199
00:15:50,154 --> 00:15:51,290
Can I look?
- Okay.

200
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:52,123
- Okay.

201
00:15:56,164 --> 00:16:00,081
(melancholic orchestral music)

202
00:16:05,588 --> 00:16:07,171
What have you done?

203
00:16:08,843 --> 00:16:10,253
- What do you mean?

204
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:12,980
- [Blanche] It's way too short.

205
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:14,263
- No, it's not, I think it looks great.

206
00:16:14,263 --> 00:16:16,733
- It's awful, it's way too short!

207
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,983
What have you done?

208
00:16:21,039 --> 00:16:24,206
- You never think I do anything right!

209
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,510
- Jane!

210
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:28,343
I'm sorry.

211
00:16:30,399 --> 00:16:33,103
I'll even it out somehow, I'm sorry!

212
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:45,490
- How'd you get in?

213
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:48,210
- Miss Hudson told me where
you keep the extra key.

214
00:16:48,210 --> 00:16:50,110
Don't worry, I put it back.

215
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:51,060
- Yeah?

216
00:16:51,060 --> 00:16:53,853
Well, she was gettin'
herself all pretty for ya.

217
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:57,020
Now you ruined it.

218
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:58,710
- Yeah, well my schedule
got all screwed up

219
00:16:58,710 --> 00:17:01,020
on account I got a call
back for that series.

220
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,710
- Yeah, well, I've been there.

221
00:17:02,710 --> 00:17:04,673
I wouldn't quit my day job just yet.

222
00:17:17,987 --> 00:17:19,983
- How're you doin' today, Blanche?

223
00:17:21,858 --> 00:17:23,208
What happened to your hair?

224
00:17:25,870 --> 00:17:26,703
- I cut it.

225
00:17:32,834 --> 00:17:34,570
Did you get your series?

226
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:36,700
- Well, I got a call back.

227
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,860
- Oh, that's wonderful.

228
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:40,288
- Yeah, well, your sister didn't seem

229
00:17:40,288 --> 00:17:41,617
to think it was any bid deal.

230
00:17:41,617 --> 00:17:43,660
- Oh, Dominick, you'll get
that series, I know you will.

231
00:17:45,390 --> 00:17:46,785
- Thanks.

232
00:17:46,785 --> 00:17:47,618
Alright.

233
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:51,603
Ready?

234
00:17:52,484 --> 00:17:53,484
Up and over.

235
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:58,040
Blanche.

236
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:00,290
Did you talk to Dr.
Shelby about your sister?

237
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:02,003
- Not yet.

238
00:18:03,670 --> 00:18:05,750
- She's gettin' worse, you know.

239
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:08,003
Saw an open bottle of vodka downstairs.

240
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:10,810
You know, the doctor said
she might do somethin' crazy

241
00:18:10,810 --> 00:18:11,930
if she started drinkin' again.

242
00:18:11,930 --> 00:18:13,568
- I thought she was getting better.

243
00:18:13,568 --> 00:18:15,700
- Yeah.

244
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:16,533
Well, she's not.

245
00:18:22,709 --> 00:18:25,792
I found this on the floor downstairs.

246
00:18:34,130 --> 00:18:36,023
- What ever made her do this?

247
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:39,120
- Sick mind, that's the
kind of stuff you see

248
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,320
scratched on public toilets.

249
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,280
- She's perverted a lovely fan letter.

250
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:46,780
- Mm-hm, reads like hate mail.
- But why?

251
00:18:46,780 --> 00:18:48,033
- Like I said, nuts-oh.

252
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:51,077
Maybe she knows about
you sellin' the house.

253
00:18:51,077 --> 00:18:53,220
(Blanche gasps)

254
00:18:53,220 --> 00:18:54,540
- She couldn't.

255
00:18:54,540 --> 00:18:55,540
- Your health drink!

256
00:18:57,590 --> 00:18:58,523
Right on time.

257
00:18:59,959 --> 00:19:02,292
(dog barks)

258
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:07,670
