00:38:59,850 --> 00:39:01,470
- You got paid for the session.

528
00:39:01,470 --> 00:39:05,538
- We want 250 more for each
publication, we count four here.

529
00:39:05,538 --> 00:39:08,140
- I'm onto something, it'll be ready cash.

530
00:39:08,140 --> 00:39:10,745
- You got a week, Billy,
then things get ugly.

531
00:39:10,745 --> 00:39:12,642
(chuckles) We're underage.

532
00:39:12,642 --> 00:39:14,330
(Billy chuckles)

533
00:39:14,330 --> 00:39:16,590
You can meet the new kid
tonight, he's got some film,

534
00:39:16,590 --> 00:39:19,670
but you gotta be a better
broker than you've been.

535
00:39:19,670 --> 00:39:21,003
- Okay, okay.

536
00:39:21,907 --> 00:39:26,907
Yeah.

537
00:39:32,688 --> 00:39:35,188
(phone rings)

538
00:39:36,117 --> 00:39:39,437
(phone rings)

539
00:39:39,437 --> 00:39:42,317
(phone rings)

540
00:39:42,317 --> 00:39:44,500
(phone rings)

541
00:39:44,500 --> 00:39:45,410
- Hello?

542
00:39:45,410 --> 00:39:47,932
- Miss Hudson, it's Billy Korn.

543
00:39:47,932 --> 00:39:50,580
- Oh, hello, Mr. Korn.

544
00:39:50,580 --> 00:39:52,730
- Please, call me Billy, Miss Hudson.

545
00:39:52,730 --> 00:39:55,773
- Oh, (chuckles) sorry, Billy.

546
00:39:56,610 --> 00:39:59,473
If I call you Billy, you'll
have to call me Jane.

547
00:40:00,990 --> 00:40:02,710
- Alright. (chuckles)

548
00:40:02,710 --> 00:40:05,690
Jane. (chuckles)

549
00:40:05,690 --> 00:40:09,810
I thought we should get
together as soon as possible.

550
00:40:09,810 --> 00:40:12,250
You know the business, time is money.

551
00:40:12,250 --> 00:40:15,543
- Yeah, well, how about right now?

552
00:40:17,230 --> 00:40:20,150
No, tell you what, give
me an hour, make it two?

553
00:40:20,150 --> 00:40:21,050
- Alright.

554
00:40:21,050 --> 00:40:24,940
- Yeah, you have my
address, 168 North Plymouth.

555
00:40:24,940 --> 00:40:26,403
Uh-huh, bye.

556
00:40:40,140 --> 00:40:40,973
- Jane.

557
00:40:42,543 --> 00:40:45,543
(dark string music)

558
00:40:54,532 --> 00:40:55,532
- It's good.

559
00:40:57,750 --> 00:40:59,050
- Is the scarf new?
- No.

560
00:41:05,561 --> 00:41:07,228
But the belt is new.

561
00:41:41,392 --> 00:41:42,453
- Mrs. Trotter!

562
00:41:42,453 --> 00:41:45,469
(upbeat electronic music)

563
00:41:45,469 --> 00:41:47,277
Mrs. Trotter!

564
00:41:47,277 --> 00:41:50,777
(upbeat electronic music)

565
00:41:59,061 --> 00:42:00,510
- Billy!

566
00:42:00,510 --> 00:42:01,790
Billy, we want you to meet someone.

567
00:42:01,790 --> 00:42:03,669
- I can't, I've got an appointment.

568
00:42:03,669 --> 00:42:07,502
- But this is the boy I
was telling you about!

569
00:42:14,479 --> 00:42:16,979
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

570
00:42:26,252 --> 00:42:27,335
- [Billy] Hm.

571
00:42:55,146 --> 00:42:58,475
(doorbell rings)

572
00:42:58,475 --> 00:42:59,308
- Hi.

573
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:03,863
Remember this outfit?

574
00:43:05,420 --> 00:43:06,693
Northern Outpost?

575
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:10,063
All the Outpost films, I wore this outfit.

576
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,823
Had it made years ago.

577
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:18,513
Put it on for you.

578
00:43:20,620 --> 00:43:24,013
- That was nice. (chuckles)

579
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:36,610
I just love these fine old homes.

580
00:43:36,610 --> 00:43:37,850
This is what Hollywood used to be.

581
00:43:37,850 --> 00:43:39,060
- It was a wonderful time.

582
00:43:39,060 --> 00:43:41,680
- I could've been Ray
Moland or Robert Taylor

583
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:43,990
taking my constitutional up your street.

584
00:43:43,990 --> 00:43:45,233
I really felt like I was back in the 40s.

585
00:43:45,233 --> 00:43:47,410
- You didn't drive?

586
00:43:47,410 --> 00:43:49,323
- No, my car's with my mechanic.

587
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:52,820
- Well, come into the living room.

588
00:43:52,820 --> 00:43:53,653
- Oh.

589
00:43:56,605 --> 00:43:59,740
Oh, this is wonderful.
(Jane giggles)

590
00:43:59,740 --> 00:44:02,190
Now, this was your parents' house?

591
00:44:02,190 --> 00:44:03,870
- Oh, yeah, yeah, but I
paid for it, you know,

592
00:44:03,870 --> 00:44:06,862
with all the money that I
earned, we all lived here,

593
00:44:06,862 --> 00:44:09,230
but of course, it wasn't
smart enough for my sister

594
00:44:09,230 --> 00:44:12,450
when she became Miss High
and Mighty, so she moved out.

595
00:44:12,450 --> 00:44:15,030
- Oh, she doesn't--

596
00:44:15,030 --> 00:44:16,570
- Oh, yeah, yeah!

597
00:44:16,570 --> 00:44:20,020
But when I had my episode,
she moved back in to take care

598
00:44:20,020 --> 00:44:22,722
of me but now I'm taking care
of her, isn't that somethin'?

599
00:44:22,722 --> 00:44:25,490
(chuckles) Here, look here, it's Daddy.

600
00:44:25,490 --> 00:44:27,163
- Oh.
- Isn't that great?

601
00:44:28,820 --> 00:44:33,570
Oh, I have all kinds, I've
got cream cake and caramel.

602
00:44:33,570 --> 00:44:36,570
I just love petit four, I
usually buy half a dozen,

603
00:44:36,570 --> 00:44:39,410
but I just limit myself to one a day.

604
00:44:39,410 --> 00:44:42,380
Got these today.
(buzzing)

605
00:44:42,380 --> 00:44:43,580
Here.

606
00:44:43,580 --> 00:44:44,890
- Oh.

607
00:44:44,890 --> 00:44:49,350
I'll try the, uh, the caramel. (laughs)

608
00:44:49,350 --> 00:44:51,460
- Oh, this is Daddy's favorite chair.

609
00:44:51,460 --> 00:44:54,340
I bought it for him.
(buzzing)

610
00:44:54,340 --> 00:44:56,190
Here, why don't you go
ahead and help yourself.

611
00:44:56,190 --> 00:44:57,690
I'll be right back, then you just join me

612
00:44:57,690 --> 00:44:59,200
in the rehearsal room over there?

613
00:44:59,200 --> 00:45:00,113
I'll be there.

614
00:45:17,010 --> 00:45:20,040
- Who's downstairs?
- It's none of your business.

615
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:22,723
Is it so hard to believe
somebody would come to visit me?

616
00:45:24,952 --> 00:45:27,070
- What are you trying to do to me?

617
00:45:27,070 --> 00:45:29,803
- You mean what are you doing to me?

618
00:45:33,300 --> 00:45:36,933
Listen to this damn buzzer for
20 years and I am sick of it.

619
00:45:38,500 --> 00:45:40,100
Oh, you didn't want your dinner?

620
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:43,490
I made it just the way you like it.

621
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:45,673
Mm!

622
00:45:46,520 --> 00:45:48,270
Onions and seasoning, this is good.

623
00:45:50,590 --> 00:45:51,780
I'll save it for Tweak when he gets back

624
00:45:51,780 --> 00:45:53,047
from obedience school.

625
00:45:53,950 --> 00:45:54,783
- What?

626
00:45:55,750 --> 00:45:58,510
- Yeah, ran into our nextdoor
neighbor this afternoon,

627
00:45:58,510 --> 00:46:01,583
and he says they found a
dog school that takes rats.

628
00:46:02,908 --> 00:46:04,980
- I'm hungry!

629
00:46:04,980 --> 00:46:06,520
- Well, of course you're hungry,

630
00:46:06,520 --> 00:46:08,127
you don't eat what I put out for you!

631
00:46:08,127 --> 00:46:10,970
- You're trying to kill me.
- (chuckles) No.

632
00:46:10,970 --> 00:46:13,508
- Yes, you are, you're
trying to starve me to death!

633
00:46:13,508 --> 00:46:15,420
You're frightened to eat!

634
00:46:15,420 --> 00:46:16,840
- I'm not trying to starve you to death.

635
00:46:16,840 --> 00:46:18,147
That would be a silly thing to do.

636
00:46:18,147 --> 00:46:22,740
- Oh, yes, yes, it would,
because if something happened

637
00:46:22,740 --> 00:46:26,100
to me, something bad, there
wouldn't be any money.

638
00:46:26,100 --> 00:46:29,960
- Yeah, there'd be money.
- Oh, but not for you!

639
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:33,970
Because they'd have to
put you away somewhere,

640
00:46:33,970 --> 00:46:36,120
and I wouldn't be there
to sign the checks!

641
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:47,123
What do you think of that?

642
00:46:50,521 --> 00:46:51,354
- Yep.

643
00:46:54,046 --> 00:46:55,363
- Good.

644
00:46:55,363 --> 00:46:57,313
Then you bring me some dinner.

645
00:46:59,580 --> 00:47:03,063
- I'm gonna have my career
again, what do you think of that?

646
00:47:18,574 --> 00:47:21,408
♪ My love will go with you ♪

647
00:47:21,408 --> 00:47:23,928
♪ Protect you and such ♪

648
00:47:23,928 --> 00:47:28,928
♪ I'll see you in the morning's day ♪

649
00:47:29,011 --> 00:47:32,594
♪ Tomorrow is not far away ♪

650
00:47:36,250 --> 00:47:37,170
- You remembered.

651
00:47:37,170 --> 00:47:39,220
- And not a dry eye in
the house, I'll bet.

652
00:47:39,220 --> 00:47:40,870
- They'll expect me to sing that.

653
00:47:42,508 --> 00:47:44,520
- It's a little dated. (chuckles)

654
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:46,540
- Oh, what about a new arrangement?

655
00:47:46,540 --> 00:47:48,750
- Well, it's a lullaby, you
can't really update that.

656
00:47:48,750 --> 00:47:50,890
You know, we oughta get the
business part out of the way

657
00:47:50,890 --> 00:47:52,890
before we go on.
- What business part?

658
00:47:52,890 --> 00:47:57,013
- You know, the ugly
money part. (chuckles)

659
00:47:57,013 --> 00:47:59,860
- (giggles) What'll it cost?
- Well, I wanna try it out.

660
00:47:59,860 --> 00:48:02,320
Test it at a club, a cabaret,
a showcase kind of thing.

661
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:03,680
That's when the agents come.
- Really?

662
00:48:03,680 --> 00:48:05,400
- Do a couple of songs,
'cause that's all the time

663
00:48:05,400 --> 00:48:08,090
they'll give us, you
know, see what happens.

664
00:48:08,090 --> 00:48:10,880
- Is that expensive?
- It could run...

665
00:48:13,597 --> 00:48:14,973
$1,000.

666
00:48:15,810 --> 00:48:19,450
But that's for the spot,
you know, advertising,

667
00:48:19,450 --> 00:48:22,030
paying the lighting man,
the costumes, arrangements,

668
00:48:22,030 --> 00:48:23,280
choreography, everything.

669
00:48:24,750 --> 00:48:27,173
If you want a little time, think it over?

670
00:48:28,450 --> 00:48:30,800
- When could we do it?
- When they got room.

671
00:48:30,800 --> 00:48:33,190
The owner's a friend of mine,
you want me to make a call?

672
00:48:33,190 --> 00:48:34,240
- Oh.

673
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:36,840
- You know, this is the kind
of break that could put us

674
00:48:36,840 --> 00:48:38,090
both right over the top.

675
00:48:38,090 --> 00:48:39,283
- Really?
- Really.

676
00:48:42,610 --> 00:48:46,705
- Yeah, go ahead, you make
that call, phone's in the hall!

677
00:48:46,705 --> 00:48:47,788
There.
- Okay.

678
00:49:05,610 --> 00:49:08,540
- Mrs. Trotter, this is your
neighbor, Blanche Hudson.

679
00:49:08,540 --> 00:49:11,060
I need your help, I'm
unable to use the phone.

680
00:49:11,060 --> 00:49:13,050
Could you please call Dr. Shelby for me?

681
00:49:13,050 --> 00:49:16,850
His number is 555-6314.

682
00:49:16,850 --> 00:49:18,500
And ask him to come over at once.

683
00:49:19,453 --> 00:49:23,093
(gasps) Please, don't tell
my sister about this message.

684
00:49:27,610 --> 00:49:31,780
For me, his number is 555-6314.

685
00:49:31,780 --> 00:49:33,900
And ask him to come over at once.

686
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:36,160
- [Billy] Okay, I'll find
out and I'll call you

687
00:49:36,160 --> 00:49:37,833
later tonight, (laughs) alright.

688
00:49:47,780 --> 00:49:50,400
- Look at this, Sword of Excellence award.

689
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:53,653
I won it when I was a little
girl for the Outpost films.

690
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:56,440
- Real nice.

691
00:49:56,440 --> 00:49:59,670
Listen, Jane, I've got
good news and bad news.

692
00:49:59,670 --> 00:50:01,320
They want both you and your sister.

693
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:04,117
- No, my sister's in a
wheelchair, it's my act, not hers.

694
00:50:04,117 --> 00:50:05,680
- I'll talk to him.

695
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:06,903
I told you, Luther the
owner's a friend of mine.

696
00:50:06,903 --> 00:50:08,949
- Well, when do we do it?
- Wednesday.

697
00:50:08,949 --> 00:50:09,820
- What? So soon?

698
00:50:09,820 --> 00:50:12,920
- I know almost all the songs
already and the choreography.

699
00:50:12,920 --> 00:50:14,130
Everything.

700
00:50:14,130 --> 00:50:19,130
You could do Orphan of Love
and, uh, There Should Be Love.

701
00:50:20,230 --> 00:50:23,353
- The music's on the piano,
There Should Be Love.

702
00:50:23,353 --> 00:50:25,410
- Alright! (laughs)

703
00:50:25,410 --> 00:50:26,243
Okay.

704
00:50:27,090 --> 00:50:28,613
Medium bounce.

705
00:50:30,680 --> 00:50:33,763
(upbeat piano music)

706
00:50:45,455 --> 00:50:47,230
(laughs) Okay.

707
00:50:47,230 --> 00:50:51,189
- Again.
(upbeat piano music)

708
00:50:51,189 --> 00:50:54,135
♪ There should be love ♪

709
00:50:54,135 --> 00:50:57,687
♪ Love should be there ♪

710
00:50:57,687 --> 00:51:00,551
♪ Not being scared ♪

711
00:51:00,551 --> 00:51:05,551
♪ Should be love ♪

712
00:51:05,562 --> 00:51:08,200
♪ There should be you ♪

713
00:51:08,200 --> 00:51:11,367
♪ You should be there ♪

714
00:51:23,330 --> 00:51:25,673
I did sing beautifully
when I was very young.

715
00:51:26,530 --> 00:51:27,363
- I know.

716
00:51:28,318 --> 00:51:29,218
(chuckles) I know.

717
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:31,353
It's okay.

718
00:51:35,170 --> 00:51:38,263
Jane, you could lip-sync to the record.

719
00:51:39,580 --> 00:51:42,440
- Who'd sing Blanche's part?
- Oh.

720
00:51:42,440 --> 00:51:44,470
- We were on the record together!

721
00:51:44,470 --> 00:51:45,610
- Alright, oh!

722
00:51:45,610 --> 00:51:48,330
Alright, we'll black out
one side of the stage.

723
00:51:48,330 --> 00:51:51,570
You'll be in a spotlight
and Blanche's voice just

724
00:51:51,570 --> 00:51:53,440
comes out of the darkness.

725
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:55,520
- Will that work?
- Jane, you're a star.

726
00:51:55,520 --> 00:51:59,570
Your sister's a star,
they're after an event.

727
00:51:59,570 --> 00:52:01,320
Now, let's give 'em one.

728
00:52:01,320 --> 00:52:02,420
You leave it to Billy.

729
00:52:04,780 --> 00:52:06,013
- You're so nice.

730
00:52:07,090 --> 00:52:09,050
(Billy chuckles)

731
00:52:09,050 --> 00:52:11,830
- Um... (chuckles)

732
00:52:11,830 --> 00:52:16,763
Well, I hate to bring this up
but I'm gonna need some money.

733
00:52:18,092 --> 00:52:18,925
- When?

734
00:52:19,860 --> 00:52:20,810
- [Billy] Tomorrow?

735
00:52:21,817 --> 00:52:22,734
- Tomorrow?

736
00:52:24,140 --> 00:52:24,990
Um...

737
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:30,603
Tomorrow I give you half?

738
00:52:31,820 --> 00:52:32,720
- That'll be fine.

739
00:52:37,030 --> 00:52:39,313
Oh, I should be going.

740
00:52:39,313 --> 00:52:42,160
- I'll drive you, where do you live?

741
00:52:42,160 --> 00:52:44,874
- Oh, you just drop me in Hollywood.

742
00:52:44,874 --> 00:52:45,707
- Yeah?

743
00:52:54,424 --> 00:52:56,079
Where do you want me to stop?

744
00:52:56,079 --> 00:52:57,735
Just here?

745
00:52:57,735 --> 00:52:58,568
Here?

746
00:52:59,670 --> 00:53:01,920
- Okay, so I'll come
by tomorrow around 10,

747
00:53:01,920 --> 00:53:04,090
and we could go to the bank together.

748
00:53:04,090 --> 00:53:05,720
- What do they want?
- No they don't want anything.

749
00:53:05,720 --> 00:53:07,817
Go away, go on.
- They scare me.

750
00:53:07,817 --> 00:53:10,410
- Jane, you go on home,
alright, there's no reason

751
00:53:10,410 --> 00:53:12,850
