01:17:43,519 --> 01:17:45,130
- Papa.

1026
01:17:45,130 --> 01:17:46,533
(melancholic orchestral music)

1027
01:17:46,533 --> 01:17:49,173
When I see this, I feel like I'm there.

1028
01:17:50,820 --> 01:17:52,477
Like no time has passed.

1029
01:17:54,430 --> 01:17:58,653
I remember the woodsy
sawdust smell of the set.

1030
01:18:00,427 --> 01:18:03,850
And also lamps that had been on too long.

1031
01:18:03,850 --> 01:18:06,653
And they smelled to me like wax melting.

1032
01:18:07,949 --> 01:18:12,170
And I can feel the hugs and I
can hear the congratulations

1033
01:18:12,170 --> 01:18:16,140
everywhere I went 'cause
I was so important then.

1034
01:18:16,140 --> 01:18:17,693
All of my pictures made money.

1035
01:18:19,205 --> 01:18:21,940
That's why they gave me this award.

1036
01:18:21,940 --> 01:18:25,723
Sword of Excellence,
Best Child Actress, 1949.

1037
01:18:28,405 --> 01:18:31,405
(suspenseful music)

1038
01:18:36,191 --> 01:18:37,024
- Jane!

1039
01:19:08,666 --> 01:19:09,499
Jane?

1040
01:19:44,651 --> 01:19:45,901
Blanche Hudson.

1041
01:19:57,763 --> 01:19:59,846
What has she done to you?

1042
01:20:12,542 --> 01:20:14,737
(music swells)

1043
01:20:14,737 --> 01:20:18,904
(gasps)
(clatter)

1044
01:20:24,394 --> 01:20:27,061
(ominous tones)

1045
01:20:47,652 --> 01:20:50,319
(ominous tones)

1046
01:21:06,013 --> 01:21:07,430
- [Jane] Blanche?

1047
01:21:11,053 --> 01:21:14,714
- I came back for the
money you owe me, Jane.

1048
01:21:14,714 --> 01:21:15,680
- What money?

1049
01:21:15,680 --> 01:21:17,660
- It's not a lot of money, Jane.

1050
01:21:17,660 --> 01:21:19,834
Not to you, it isn't.

1051
01:21:19,834 --> 01:21:21,347
But it is to me.

1052
01:21:21,347 --> 01:21:23,193
- Always about money, Blanche.

1053
01:21:24,130 --> 01:21:25,433
- I need it badly, Jane.

1054
01:21:27,320 --> 01:21:30,233
If you don't have it, maybe
we could work something out.

1055
01:21:32,460 --> 01:21:34,363
I wanna be your friend, Jane.

1056
01:21:36,260 --> 01:21:41,072
I consider myself a very
good friend, am I right?

1057
01:21:41,072 --> 01:21:45,905
(flesh squelches)
(gasps)

1058
01:21:48,047 --> 01:21:50,130
(groans)

1059
01:21:53,366 --> 01:21:55,949
(music swells)

1060
01:22:16,713 --> 01:22:17,546
- Billy.

1061
01:22:49,311 --> 01:22:51,811
(birds tweet)

1062
01:23:15,256 --> 01:23:16,089
Blanche?

1063
01:23:28,500 --> 01:23:30,063
Blanche, we can go away now.

1064
01:23:32,010 --> 01:23:33,203
Just like you wanted.

1065
01:23:35,640 --> 01:23:36,963
Everyone's gone.

1066
01:23:37,940 --> 01:23:38,823
They've all gone.

1067
01:23:40,290 --> 01:23:41,563
Do you hear me, Blanche?

1068
01:23:42,570 --> 01:23:43,770
Do you hear what I said?

1069
01:24:01,200 --> 01:24:02,513
We can go to the beach.

1070
01:24:03,800 --> 01:24:05,313
You like the beach, remember?

1071
01:24:07,090 --> 01:24:08,590
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

1072
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:11,913
Say yes.

1073
01:24:17,030 --> 01:24:17,863
- Yeah.

1074
01:24:20,520 --> 01:24:21,423
- Gotta go now.

1075
01:24:22,940 --> 01:24:23,913
Gotta leave now.

1076
01:24:27,050 --> 01:24:28,023
The dark here.

1077
01:24:29,090 --> 01:24:30,623
It's always cold and dark.

1078
01:24:32,460 --> 01:24:33,563
Wanna see the sun.

1079
01:24:35,750 --> 01:24:37,150
Don't wanna be cold anymore.

1080
01:24:40,271 --> 01:24:41,104
- Yeah.

1081
01:25:01,730 --> 01:25:03,380
- [Jane] Look what I got for you.

1082
01:25:04,429 --> 01:25:05,262
There.

1083
01:25:08,641 --> 01:25:10,037
- Jane.

1084
01:25:10,037 --> 01:25:11,953
I'm thirsty, please.

1085
01:25:13,280 --> 01:25:14,980
- [Jane] Find someplace to get it.

1086
01:25:17,170 --> 01:25:19,423
- Stop someone, please.

1087
01:25:20,784 --> 01:25:22,770
I need a doctor.

1088
01:25:22,770 --> 01:25:26,480
- [Jane] No, 'cause then
they'll make me go away,

1089
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:27,813
and I wanna stay with you.

1090
01:25:31,113 --> 01:25:32,033
- I'm dying.

1091
01:25:33,610 --> 01:25:34,610
- And I'll be alone.

1092
01:25:36,918 --> 01:25:39,335
(bell rings)

1093
01:25:46,463 --> 01:25:48,880
(bell rings)

1094
01:26:03,260 --> 01:26:04,460
- Listen.

1095
01:26:04,460 --> 01:26:07,700
That night I was driving
in the car and you weren't.

1096
01:26:07,700 --> 01:26:12,700
You were full of drink,
full of dope and I hated you

1097
01:26:13,570 --> 01:26:17,530
because you had so much
love when we were young

1098
01:26:17,530 --> 01:26:22,530
and you tried to keep
me from having anything.

1099
01:26:22,620 --> 01:26:26,630
- [Jane] Do you remember we
used to find bottles that were

1100
01:26:26,630 --> 01:26:30,080
all worn, smooth from the ocean?

1101
01:26:30,080 --> 01:26:32,110
They were like samphires and emeralds,

1102
01:26:32,110 --> 01:26:33,360
and that kind of stuff?

1103
01:26:33,360 --> 01:26:35,140
I liked that, those were the best times.

1104
01:26:35,140 --> 01:26:38,500
- I lied to you, I cheated you.

1105
01:26:38,500 --> 01:26:43,500
I wanted you dead, I
wanted to run you down.

1106
01:26:44,390 --> 01:26:48,570
- [Jane] No I was driving that
car, Blanche, and I hurt you.

1107
01:26:48,570 --> 01:26:52,490
- No, I was behind the wheel,

1108
01:26:52,490 --> 01:26:56,422
and you were too drunk.

1109
01:26:56,422 --> 01:26:59,560
- No, that's not the way it was, Blanche.

1110
01:26:59,560 --> 01:27:00,393
- I was...

1111
01:27:02,460 --> 01:27:05,857
Thrown out of the car
and you were too drunk

1112
01:27:07,327 --> 01:27:10,860
and you were frightened and you ran away,

1113
01:27:10,860 --> 01:27:15,860
and when they found me, I let them believe

1114
01:27:16,580 --> 01:27:21,140
you did it and they found
and you were frightened

1115
01:27:22,498 --> 01:27:27,498
and confused and I was lying by the car,

1116
01:27:27,570 --> 01:27:29,800
and they assumed you did it.

1117
01:27:29,800 --> 01:27:30,633
- No.

1118
01:27:32,820 --> 01:27:34,080
- What you thought...

1119
01:27:35,910 --> 01:27:36,880
You did...

1120
01:27:39,090 --> 01:27:40,053
I did.

1121
01:27:41,423 --> 01:27:43,373
To myself.

1122
01:27:44,870 --> 01:27:47,777
Because I wanted to hurt you.

1123
01:27:57,333 --> 01:28:01,833
- You mean, all these years,
we could've been friends?

1124
01:28:03,868 --> 01:28:06,817
(melancholic string music)

1125
01:28:06,817 --> 01:28:10,085
(Blanche sobs)

1126
01:28:10,085 --> 01:28:12,418
(Jane sobs)

1127
01:28:54,370 --> 01:28:56,870
- Here you are, okay.
- Thanks!

1128
01:29:11,373 --> 01:29:14,123
(Blanche groans)

1129
01:29:15,308 --> 01:29:17,618
There, I got us strawberry.

1130
01:29:17,618 --> 01:29:19,213
You like strawberry.

1131
01:29:19,213 --> 01:29:20,046
Here.

1132
01:29:27,239 --> 01:29:28,072
- Jane.

1133
01:29:31,495 --> 01:29:32,328
I'm sorry.

1134
01:29:34,076 --> 01:29:35,576
I'm so very sorry.

1135
01:29:38,675 --> 01:29:41,258
- Nose will get red in the sun.

1136
01:29:48,154 --> 01:29:50,404
(chuckles)

1137
01:29:58,610 --> 01:30:00,260
Maybe we could live at the beach.

1138
01:30:02,704 --> 01:30:06,037
(dark orchestral music)

1139
01:30:15,880 --> 01:30:16,713
- Miss?

1140
01:30:18,110 --> 01:30:19,680
Miss?

1141
01:30:19,680 --> 01:30:21,960
Is that your white Cadillac over there?

1142
01:30:21,960 --> 01:30:23,309
- Yeah.

1143
01:30:23,309 --> 01:30:24,409
- Are you Miss Hudson?

1144
01:30:25,595 --> 01:30:27,830
- (chuckles) Yeah.

1145
01:30:27,830 --> 01:30:31,900
I'm Baby Jane Hudson and this
is my sister, Blanche Hudson.

1146
01:30:31,900 --> 01:30:33,133
She's a movie star, too.

1147
01:30:36,730 --> 01:30:39,330
- See if she can talk.
- Miss, can you hear me?

1148
01:30:39,330 --> 01:30:40,720
Can you hear me?

1149
01:30:40,720 --> 01:30:41,780
Miss.

1150
01:30:41,780 --> 01:30:43,830
- Call for an ambulance.
- Right.

1151
01:30:43,830 --> 01:30:47,620
This is 14-23 requesting
an ambulance, Venice Beach.

1152
01:30:47,620 --> 01:30:49,400
100 feet north of the pier.

1153
01:30:49,400 --> 01:30:51,450
It's a code three, we have a woman down.

1154
01:30:51,450 --> 01:30:54,170
Pulse is low, breathing shallow.

1155
01:30:54,170 --> 01:30:56,930
- [Dispatch] Yeah, we copy
14-23, what have you got?

1156
01:30:56,930 --> 01:30:59,900
- [Officer] That's code three,
just north of Venice Pier.

1157
01:30:59,900 --> 01:31:01,300
- [Dispatch] We copy, 14-23.

1158
01:31:05,100 --> 01:31:07,767
- You're gonna be alright, miss.

1159
01:31:31,279 --> 01:31:32,279
Miss Hudson!

1160
01:31:34,563 --> 01:31:35,563
Jane Hudson!

1161
01:31:55,109 --> 01:31:55,942
- Papa!

1162
01:32:08,600 --> 01:32:10,542
Let's live at the beach.

1163
01:32:10,542 --> 01:32:11,375
Can we?

1164
01:32:34,488 --> 01:32:37,821
(dark orchestral music)

